cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques for classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses pre-trained embeddings and a model for distillation, which are common techniques in deep learning and machine learning research, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper deals with semantic relations and classification, which are also relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of neural networks, which is a common technique in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of embeddings for image classification, which is relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
